# Finding 027
- Severity: Low
- Pattern type: AI slop; Repeated router guard logic
- File + line(s): `apps/jskit-value-app/src/app/router/guards.console.js:165-266`
- Why it can drift/fail: Multiple `beforeLoad*` guards repeat the same console runtime checks (session availability, authentication, console access, invite handling) with minor variations. This is copy-paste boilerplate that risks divergence when rules change.
- Concrete impact: Inconsistent guard behavior across console routes and higher maintenance cost when access policy evolves.
- Exact remediation: Extract shared guard helpers (e.g., `requireConsoleAuth`, `requireConsoleAccess`, `redirectIfInvited`) and compose them per route to make policy changes centralized and explicit.

